# ☁️ Remote MCP

A **Remote MCP Server** runs on a remote machine or cloud server. Communication occurs over **HTTP**, **HTTP/SSE**, or **Streamable HTTP**.

The AI model connects to the remote server, which then interacts with cloud services or enterprise systems.

## Features

* Runs on a cloud or remote server
* Uses HTTP-based communication
* Requires internet connectivity
* Supports OAuth authentication
* Can be shared among multiple users
* Ideal for SaaS and enterprise integrations

## Common Use Cases

* GitHub
* Stripe
* Salesforce
* Jira
* Notion
* Internal APIs
* Cloud databases

### Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    U[User]
    O[OpenAI Responses API]
    M[Remote MCP Server]
    G[GitHub]
    S[Stripe]
    N[Notion]
    A[Cloud APIs]

    U --> O
    O -->|HTTPS| M
    M --> G
    M --> S
    M --> N
    M --> A
```

